    <h>cha</h>

    <p><g>cha</g> is the negative declarative verb particle.</p>

    <section>
        <h>dependents</h>
        <section id="deps-comp">
            <h>complement</h>
            <p>The complement of <g>cha</g> is a dependent verb form.</p>
            <p>Some examples with the predicative verb <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a>
                <en>be</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Chan <m>eil</m> e fuar an diugh.</gd>
                        <tr>It is not cold today.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 11</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Cha <m>robh</m> mi anns an taigh.</gd>
                        <tr>I was not at home.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 17</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-root">
            <h>root</h>
            <p><g>cha</g> can be used as the root of a statement.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd><m>Chan</m> eil an seòmar seo blàth?</gd>
                        <tr>This room is not warm.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd><m>Cha</m> robh Seònaid anns an achadh còmhla ri Seumas.</gd>
                        <tr>Janet is not in the field along with James.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                <li>
                    <gd>Dé tha ceàrr air a’ ghille seo? Tha a cheann goirt. An robh e anns an sgoil
                        an diugh? <m>Cha robh</m>, bha e anns an taigh fad an latha.</gd>
                    <tr>What is wrong with this boy? His head is sore. Was he in the school today? No, he
                        was in the house all day long.</tr>
                    <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>




